<item>
            <title>[FLINK-5518] HadoopInputFormat throws NPE when close() is called before open()</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-5518</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When developing a simple Flink applications reading ORC files it crashes with NullPointerException when number of instances/executor threads is higher then the number of files because it is trying to close a HadoopInputFormat which is trying to close RecordReader which was not yet initialized as there is no file for which it should have been opened. The issue is caused when&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void run(SourceContext&amp;lt;OUT&amp;gt; ctx) &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; Exception {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
...
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;while&lt;/span&gt; (isRunning) {
	    format.open(splitIterator.next());
...
    } &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;finally&lt;/span&gt; {
	format.close();
...
    }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;in file &lt;tt&gt;InputFormatSourceFunction.java&lt;/tt&gt; which calls&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void close() &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; IOException {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// enforce sequential close() calls
&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;synchronized&lt;/span&gt; (CLOSE_MUTEX) {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.recordReader.close();
    }
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;from &lt;tt&gt;HadoopInputFormatBase.java&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As there is just this one implementation of the &lt;tt&gt;close()&lt;/tt&gt; method it may be enough just to add a null check for the &lt;tt&gt;this.recordReader&lt;/tt&gt; in there.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
